{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Typically, this is the dataset used to train the prediction model.",
    "However, in the federated setting, local training sets belong to different enti-ties and cannot be shared due to privacy issues.",
    "Therefore, the server has no reference data to be used as background.",
    "Federated SHAP proposed in [21] represents a possible strategy to overcome this issue and to achieve federated explanations by exploiting the additive property of the Shapley values.In the federated SHAP procedure, first of all, each client estimates the Shapley values using the local dataset as background dataset; then the values are transmitted to the server that evaluates their average.",
    "In this way, the data privacy is preserved, since the raw data are never shared."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Federated SHAP proposed in [21] represents a possible strategy to overcome this issue and to achieve federated explanations by exploiting the additive property of the Shapley values.In the federated SHAP procedure, first of all, each client estimates the Shapley values using the local dataset as background dataset; then the values are transmitted to the server that evaluates their average."
